Titolo: KiKi KaiKai

Anno: 1986

Descrizione: KiKi KaiKai (奇々怪界, lit. "Mysterious Ghost World") is a shoot 'em up action video game developed and published by Taito for arcades in 1986. Since then, the game has received a number of home ports, both as a stand-alone title and as part of compilations. The bootleg version of the game is called Knight Boy.Set in Feudal Japan, the player must assume the role of a Shinto shrine maiden named "Sayo-chan" who must use her o-fuda scrolls and ohari Gohei  wand to defeat a number of renegade spirits and monsters from Japanese mythology.  The game is noteworthy for using a traditional fantasy setting in a genre otherwise filled with science fiction motifs.

